A man has been charged with assisted attempted suicide following an incident where he allegedly provided an injured man with the means to set himself on fire, the Crown Prosecution Service said.

Kevin Howe, 19, was charged following an incident in his home town of Bishop Auckland, County Durham, on May 26 in which a man suffered severe burns.

