Elizabeth Reid, specialist prosecutor in the CPS’s special crime division, said: 'I have concluded that Kevin Howe should face one charge of assisted attempted suicide in relation to an incident on 26 May 2013 in Bishop Auckland, in which a man was severely burnt.

'It is alleged that Kevin Howe provided the injured man with the means to set himself on fire.

'In accordance with our duty to keep all cases under review, I have now concluded that there is sufficient evidence and that it is in the public interest to replace this charge with one of assisted attempted suicide.

